<p class="mb-12 text-xl">The state of Wisconsin has been instrumental in defining the relationship between scientific discovery and society. More than a century ago, the <a href="https://www.wisc.edu/wisconsin-idea/">Wisconsin Idea</a> was articulated to explain that <em>“university research should be applied to solve problems and improve health, quality of life, the environment, and agriculture for all citizens of the state”</em>. This philosophy is still strongly rooted in Wisconsin and broadly drives scientific research in a deep commitment to enhancing public health. As a postdoctoral trainee in our state, you will become part of a long tradition of research excellence and a torchbearer for scientific discovery that benefits all people.</p>

